transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you so much for your patience.

Speaker 2: Hi.

Speaker 1: How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: I'd like to cancel my subscription, please.

Speaker 1: Okay. Let me pull up your account here, sir.

Speaker 2: Can you just a moment?

Speaker 1: Okay, Mr. Roberts. I have your account here.

Speaker 2: And I see that currently, because we're not a subscription, we're a telehealth.

Speaker 1: And so your prescription was made available with refills, which you can determine how

Speaker 2: is not until March of this year.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: And I didn't, I don't, I don't want the order, though.

Speaker 1: I wanted to stop the order.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: How did it go with the results with the new AGD?

Speaker 2: What's that?

Speaker 1: How did, did you get the results you wanted from the new AGD Viagra that you got?

Speaker 2: I don't know what you're saying.

Speaker 1: How did the Viagra 100 milligram work out for you?

Speaker 2: Oh, well, I don't need them anymore, and that's why I wanted to cancel it.

Speaker 1: Okay. I just wanted to make sure that you had gotten those desired results and it worked for you

Speaker 2: and you didn't experience any side effects or anything.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: They worked fine, but I just don't need them anymore.

Speaker 1: Okay. If I cancel your account today, sir, it will cancel your prescription with refills, so

Speaker 2: you won't be able to place another order.

Speaker 1: Are you sure you don't want to set up your account by putting a pause on it?

Speaker 2: And you can always extend that hold if needed?

Speaker 1: That way, you can...

Speaker 2: No, that's, that's fine.

Speaker 1: I'll just cancel it, because I don't want to forget and then get charged, because I

Speaker 2: have back surgery and I'm not working much anymore, and I don't want to get charged for

Speaker 1: it.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: No, absolutely.

Speaker 2: We would never want to charge you unless you were ready for your refill.

Speaker 1: I can extend the hold until end of April, if you wanted to, and I can...

Speaker 2: No, that's fine.

Speaker 1: If we can just cancel it.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: I've gone ahead and done that for you.

Speaker 2: You're all set, sir.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Mr. Roberts?

Speaker 1: Yeah?

Speaker 2: Are you still there?

Speaker 1: Uh-huh.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I'm still here.

Speaker 1: I've canceled your account.

Speaker 2: I've canceled your account.

Speaker 1: You're all set.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: So I won't get charged or nothing?

Speaker 2: Yes, that's correct.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Thank you very much.

Speaker 1: I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: No problem.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Have a good day.

Speaker 2: Bye.

Speaker 1: You too.
